    "Using small batch sizes reduces the throughput, thus limiting the aggregate request rate; if we opt for large batch sizes to ensure enough throughput, the inference latency increases, thus challenging the SLOs of the assigned clients as specified in Eq.",
    "We observe that, given a fixed batch size, the client-DNN mapping problem reduces to a standard 0-1 knapsack problem, where we treat clients as items, the request rates of clients as weights and values, and the maximum throughput of the DNN for the given batch size as the knapsack capacity.",
